rComments: His lectures were boring and tests were really hard.

Looks like a nice guy, but lectures were so difficult to follow because he's sharing so much personal stories. Slides are correct but the subject itself was so boring: Money Banking and FInancial Markets in Canada. The group project topic was not so inspirational: Life Insurance Industry.
really really really a bad teacher...

He's an extremely nice prof, but not a good teacher (and I love the guy, but it's true.) He tried to relate some of what we learned to real-world examples (the GOP primaries polls at the time) and that was interesting, but otherwise, his lectures are EXTREMELY abstract and hard to follow. If you get an A in his class, he takes you out for lunch.
Hard class, bad prof, thinks we are phd students
A tough teacher who doesn't care much for your comments.
